on the Psalter, such as handling a physical copy, reading from it, interpreting it exegetically, singing it as liturgy, invoking it as magic and reciting it as an act of piety. His book draws from and contributes to the fields of ancient Judaism, biblical reception, book history and the history of reading.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJewsxAntiquities. 0aJewsxBooks and readingxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aJudaismxCustoms and practicesxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh  aBiblical Reception.  aLiturgy.  aMagic.  aPiety.  aPsalter.  aReading.  aSecond Temple.  aTalmudic.  aauthority.  adaily life.  adiaspora.  aexegesis.  alinear reading.  aperformance.  apraise.  apsalmody.  apslams.  arabbinic thought.  aritual practice.  ascripture.  ascroll.  asecond century.  aseventh century.  atannaim.  atannaitic period.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079137240uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781512824193?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512824193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781512824193/original  a978-3-11-079137-2  University of Pennsylvania Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb20